comments.body:
The plan is to get CRI-O using libpod as a library.

@baude Opened a PR a month or so ago to start moving CRI-O to libpod for image management.
@vrothberg recently got pkg/apparmor from libpod integrated to CRI-O.  

We put some of this work on hold, to be able to get podman to 1.0 status.  But we plan on getting back to it very soon.

I think creating a TODO list is a good idea.

The biggest concern over this merger is going to be performance and stability.  CRI-O has much larger performance requirements then podman.

@mrunalp mheon WDYT?
